<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#SPN-20161231X10K_HTM_TABLE_OF_CONTENT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 6PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Stock-Based Compensation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company records compensation costs relating to share-based payment transactions and includes such costs in general and administrative expenses in the consolidated statements of operations.&nbsp;&nbsp;The cost is measured at the grant date, based on the calculated fair value of the award, and is recognized as an expense over the employee&#x2019;s requisite service period (generally the vesting period of the equity award).&nbsp;&nbsp;Excess tax benefits of awards that are recognized in equity related to stock option exercises and restricted stock vesting are reflected as financing cash flows.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Derivative Instruments and Hedging Activities
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company recognizes all derivative instruments as either assets or liabilities in the balance sheet at their respective fair values.&nbsp;&nbsp;Interest rate swap agreements that are effective at hedging the fair value of fixed-rate debt agreements are designated and accounted for as fair value hedges.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company also assesses, both at inception of the hedging relationship and on an ongoing basis, whether the derivatives used in hedging relationships are highly effective in offsetting changes in fair value.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In an attempt to achieve a more balanced debt portfolio between fixed and variable interest, the Company has entered into interest rate swaps.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under these agreements, the Company was entitled to receive semi-annual interest payments at a fixed rate and was obligated to make quarterly interest payments at a variable rate.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company had fixed-rate interest on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	77%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	62%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of its long-term debt at December 31, 2016 and 2015, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company had notional amounts of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$300
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to interest rate swaps with a variable interest rate, adjusted every
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	90
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	days, based on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	LIBOR plus a fixed margin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	at December 31, 2016 and 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;Subsequent to year-end, during January 2017, the Company sold these interest rate swaps to the counterparties for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$0.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Self-Insurance Reserves
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company is self-insured, through deductibles and retentions, up to certain levels for losses under its insurance programs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company accrues for these liabilities based on estimates of the ultimate cost of claims incurred as of the balance sheet date.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company regularly reviews the estimates of reported and unreported claims and provides for losses through reserves.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company obtains actuarial reviews to evaluate the reasonableness of internal estimates for losses related to workers&#x2019; compensation, auto liability and group medical on an annual basis.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Recently Issued Accounting Guidance
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In January, 2017, the Financial Accounting Standards Board (FASB) issued accounting standards update (ASU) 2017-04,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Intangibles- Goodwill and Other (Topic 350): Simplifying the Test for Goodwill Impairment.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The amendments eliminate Step 2 from the goodwill impairment test.&nbsp;&nbsp;The annual, or interim, goodwill impairment test is performed by comparing the fair value of a reporting unit with its carrying amount.&nbsp;&nbsp;An impairment charge should be recognized for the amount by which the carrying amount exceeds the reporting unit&#x2019;s fair value.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amendments should be applied on a prospective basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;The new standard is effective for the Company on January 1, 2020, early adoption is permitted for interim or annual goodwill impairment tests performed on testing dates after January 1, 2017.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company will adopt the accounting guidance as of January 1, 2017.&nbsp;&nbsp;The adoption of this ASU will not have a material impact on the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In January, 2017, the FASB issued ASU 2017-01,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Business Combinations (Topic 805): Clarifying the Definition of a Business.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The amendments affect all companies and other reporting organizations that must determine whether they have acquired or sold a business.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amendments are intended to help companies and other organizations evaluate whether transactions should be accounted for as acquisitions (or disposals) of assets or businesses.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amendments provide a more robust framework to use in determining when a set of assets and activities is a business.&nbsp;&nbsp;The new standard is effective for the Company beginning on January 1, 2018.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company does not expect the adoption of this ASU to have a material impact on its consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In November, 2016, the FASB issued ASU 2016-18,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Statements of Cash Flows (Topic 230): Restricted Cash.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The guidance in this update require that a statement of cash flows explain the change during the period in the total of cash, cash equivalents, and amounts generally described as restricted cash or restricted cash equivalents.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, amounts generally described as restricted cash and restricted cash equivalents should be included with cash and cash equivalents when reconciling the beginning-of-period and end-of-period total amounts shown on the statement of cash flows.&nbsp;&nbsp;The new standard is effective for the Company beginning on January 1, 2018 and should be applied on a retrospective basis. The Company does not expect the adoption of this ASU to have a material impact on its consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In October, 2016, the FASB issued ASU 2016-16,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Income Taxes (Topic 740): Intra-Entity Transfers of Assets Other Than Inventory.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The guidance in this update requires entities to recognize at the transaction date the income tax consequences of intercompany asset transfers other than inventory. The new standard is effective for the Company beginning on January 1, 2018.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company is evaluating the effect that ASU 2016-16 will have on its consolidated financial statements and related disclosures.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	42
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage43"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#SPN-20161231X10K_HTM_TABLE_OF_CONTENT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 6PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In March, 2016, the FASB issued ASU 2016-09,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Compensation &#x2013; Stock Compensation: Improvements to Employee Share-Based Payment Accounting,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	which relates to the accounting for employee share-based payments.&nbsp;&nbsp;The guidance in this update addresses several aspects of the accounting for share-based payments, including income tax consequences, classification of awards as either equity or liabilities and classification on the statement of cash flows.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company will adopt the accounting guidance as of January 1, 2017. The adoption of this ASU will not have a material impact on the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In February 2016, the FASB issued ASU No. 2016-02,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Leases
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, which requires lessees to recognize the assets and liabilities arising from leases on the balance sheet.&nbsp;&nbsp;This new guidance will require the lessee to recognize a lease liability equal to the present value of the lease payments and a right-of-use asset representing its right to use the underlying asset for the lease term for all leases longer than 12 months.&nbsp;&nbsp;For leases with a term of 12 month or less, a lessee is permitted to make an accounting policy election by class of underlying asset not to recognize lease assets and liabilities and recognize the lease expense for such leases generally on a straight-line basis over the lease term.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Under the new guidance, the Company will revise its leasing policies to require most of the leases, where the Company is the lessee, to be recognized on the balance sheet as a lease and lease liability.&nbsp;&nbsp;Further, the Company will separate leases from other contracts where the Company is either the lessor or lessee when the rights conveyed under the contracts indicate there is a lease.&nbsp;&nbsp;At this time, the Company cannot calculate the impact the new standard will have on the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements, the Company anticipates that its assets and liabilities will increase by a significant amount.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The new standard is effective for the Company beginning on January 1, 2019.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In July 2015, the FASB issued ASU No. 2015-11,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Inventory &#x2013; Simplifying the Measurement of Inventory
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, which applies to inventory measured using first-in, first-out or average cost.&nbsp;&nbsp;The guidance in this update states that inventory within its scope shall be measured at the lower of cost or net realizable value, and when the net realizable value of inventory is lower than its cost, the difference shall be recognized as a loss in earnings.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company will adopt the accounting guidance as of January 1, 2017.&nbsp;&nbsp;The adoption of this ASU will not have a material impact on the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In May 2014, the FASB issued ASU No. 2014-09,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue from Contracts with Customers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, which will replace most existing revenue recognition guidance in GAAP.&nbsp;&nbsp;The guidance in this update requires an entity to recognize the amount of revenue that it expects to be entitled for the transfer of promised goods or services to customers.&nbsp;&nbsp;The new standard is effective for the Company on January 1, 2018. The Company is in the process of determining the impacts of the new standard on its various revenue streams.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#x2019;s approach includes performing a detailed review of key contracts representative of the different businesses and comparing historical accounting policies and practices to the new accounting guidance.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#x2019;s services and rental contracts are primarily short-term in nature, and therefore, based on the initial assessment, the Company does not expect the adoption of this ASU to have a material impact on its consolidated financial statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;Remaining implementation matters include establishing new policies, procedures, and controls and quantifying any adoption date adjustments.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company will adopt this standard utilizing the modified retrospective method.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Subsequent Events
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In accordance with authoritative guidance,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the Company has evaluated and disclosed all material subsequent events
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	that occurred after the balance sheet date, but before financial statements were issued
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Reduction in Value of Goodwill
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During 2016, the Company recorded $330.5 million reduction in value of goodwill relating to its Onshore Completion and Workover Services and Production Services segments.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company determined that the implied fair value of its goodwill for the Onshore Completion and Workover Services segment was less than its carrying value and recorded a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$140.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million impairment of the Onshore Completion and Workover Services segment&#x2019;s goodwill.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the Company determined that the implied fair value of its goodwill for the Production Services segment was less than its carrying value and recorded a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$190.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million impairment of the Production Services segment&#x2019;s goodwill.&nbsp;&nbsp;The reduction in value of goodwill in the Onshore Completion and Workover Services and Production Services segments was primarily driven by further deterioration of market conditions during 2016 and the Company&#x2019;s forecast did not indicate a timely recovery sufficient to support the carrying values of the goodwill.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During 2015, the Company recorded $1,326.7 million reduction in value of goodwill relating to its Onshore Completion and Workover Services and Production Services segments.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company determined that the implied fair value of its goodwill for the Onshore Completion and Workover Services segment was less than its carrying value and recorded a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$740.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million impairment of the Onshore Completion and Workover Services segment&#x2019;s goodwill.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the Company determined that the implied fair value of its goodwill for the Production Services segment was less than its carrying value and recorded a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$586.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million impairment of the Production Services segment&#x2019;s goodwill.&nbsp;&nbsp;The reduction in value of goodwill in the Onshore Completion and Workover Services and Production Services segments was primarily driven by deteriorated market conditions during the year and the Company&#x2019;s forecast did not indicate a timely recovery sufficient to support the carrying values of the goodwill.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Reduction in Value of Long-Lived Assets
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During 2016, the Company recorded $143.8 million in connection with the reduction in value of its long-lived assets.&nbsp;&nbsp;The reduction in value of assets was comprised of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$4.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to equipment and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$45.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to intangibles in the fluid management business in the Onshore Completion and Workover Services segment and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$21.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to equipment and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$21.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to intangibles, primarily relating to the cementing business in the Production Services segment.&nbsp;&nbsp;Also, the Company recorded
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$25.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to the reduction in carrying values of certain accommodation units included in the Drilling Products and Services segment.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the Company recorded
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$25.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to the reduction in carrying values of the marine vessels and equipment in the conventional decommissioning division in its Technical Solutions segment.&nbsp;&nbsp;The reduction in value of assets recorded during 2016 was primarily driven by the decline in demand for these services.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During 2015, the Company recorded $330.2 million in connection with the reduction in value of its long-lived assets.&nbsp;&nbsp;The reduction in value of assets was comprised of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$89.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to equipment and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$59.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to intangibles in the coiled tubing business and pressure control tools businesses within the Production Services segment.&nbsp;&nbsp;The reduction in value of assets also included
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$68.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to the reduction in carrying values of the marine vessels and equipment and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$56.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million related to impairment of the Gulf of Mexico oil and gas property which is included in the Technical Solutions segment.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the reduction in value of assets included a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$40.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million charge, primarily related to reduction in carrying values of certain domestic and international accommodation units and premium drill pipe included in the Drilling Products and Services segment and a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$15.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million charge related to mechanical drilling rigs included in the Onshore Completion and Workover Services segment.&nbsp;&nbsp;The reduction in value of assets recorded during 2015 was primarily driven by the decline in demand for these services.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Retirements of Long-Lived Assets
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During 2016, the Company recorded
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$26.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million, primarily in the Drilling Products and Services segment for retirement and abandonment of excess and inoperable and/or functionally obsolete long-lived assets that would require a significant cost to refurbish.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During 2015, the Company recorded $42.5 million for retirement and abandonment of inoperable and/or functionally obsolete long-lived assets that would require a significant cost to refurbish.&nbsp;&nbsp;The total amount recorded includes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$27.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million for the Onshore Completion and Workover Services segment and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$15.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million for the Production Services segment.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Reduction in Value of Assets Related to Sale of Coiled Tubing Business in Mexico
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During 2015, the Company sold its Mexico based coiled tubing business and related assets.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company received proceeds in the form of cash and a note receivable.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company recorded a full valuation allowance on the note receivable in the amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$16.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million because its collectability was not reasonably assured.&nbsp;&nbsp;In connection with the sale, the Company recorded a $39.4 million reduction in value of assets, primarily related to property, plant and equipment and intangible assets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Other Charges
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During 2016, the Company recorded
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$39.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million primarily relating to severance and facility closures.&nbsp;&nbsp;At December 31, 2016, the accrued lease termination liability balances were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$4.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$7.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million, included in accrued expenses and other long-term liabilities, respectively, on the consolidated balance sheet.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During 2015, in connection with the reorganization of several of its businesses, the Company recorded
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$46.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million relating to severance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	expense and reorganization costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Included in the total reorganization costs is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$20.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million relating to the impairment of certain real estate operating leases included in the Onshore Completion and Workover Services segment.&nbsp;&nbsp;At December 31, 2015, the accrued lease termination liability balances were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$7.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$11.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million, included in accrued expenses and other long-term liabilities, respectively, on the consolidated balance sheet.&nbsp;&nbsp;

	Credit Facility
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	At December 31, 2015, the Company had a credit facility that was comprised of a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$600.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million revolving line of credit and a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$325.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million term loan.&nbsp;&nbsp;In February 2016, t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	he Company amended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	its credit facility
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amendment, among other things, r
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	educed the siz
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	e of the facility to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$470.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, extended the maturity
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	date to 2019 and eliminated the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	term loan component.&nbsp;&nbsp;In July 2016, the Company amended the credit facility.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amendment, among other things, reduced the size of the facility to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$400.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million, suspended the
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Total stock-based compensation expense is reflected in general and administrative expenses in the consolidated statements of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Stock Options
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Stock options are granted with an exercise price equal to the market price of our ordinary shares at the date of grant.&nbsp;&nbsp;The stock options generally vest in equal installments over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	years and expire in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ten
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	years from the grant date.&nbsp;&nbsp;Non-vested stock options are generally forfeited upon termination of employment.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company recognizes compensation expense for stock option grants based on the fair value at the date of grant using the Black-Scholes-Merton option pricing model.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company uses historical data, among other factors, to estimate the expected volatility and the expected life of the stock options.&nbsp;&nbsp;The risk-free rate is based on the U.S. Treasury yield curve in effect at the time of grant for the expected life of the stock option.&nbsp;&nbsp;The dividend yield is based on our historical
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and projected
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	dividend payouts.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	47
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The total fair value of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	restricted stock vested during 2016, 2015 and 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$6.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$12.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$23.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million, respectively.&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Restricted Stock Units
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Beginning in 2014, restricted stock unit awards (RSUs) were granted to eligible employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	instead of restricted stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Prior to 2014, only non-employee d
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	irectors were granted RSUs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;RSUs granted to employees vest in equal annual installments over three years.&nbsp;&nbsp;On the vesting date, each RSU is converted to one share of the Company&#x2019;s common stock having an aggregate value determined by the Company&#x2019;s closing stock price on the vesting date.&nbsp;&nbsp;Holders of RSUs are not entitled to any rights of a stockholder, su
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ch as the right to vote shares.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Each non-employee director is issued annually a number of RSUs having an aggregate dollar value determined by the Company&#x2019;s Board of Directors.&nbsp;&nbsp;The exact number of RSUs granted is determined by dividing the aggregate dollar value determined by the Company&#x2019;s Board of Directors by the fair market value of the Company&#x2019;s common stock on the day of the annual stockholders&#x2019; meeting.&nbsp;&nbsp;If the director&#x2019;s election occurs at a time other than at the annual meeting, the director will receive a pro-rata number of RSUs based on the number of months between his or her election date and the anniversary of the last annual stockholder meeting.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each RSU granted prior to 2013 represents the right to receive from the Company, within 30 days of the date the director ceases to serve on the Board, one share of the Company&#x2019;s common stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;The RSUs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	granted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	will vest and pay out in shares of the Company&#x2019;s common stock in the year following the grant date on the date of Company&#x2019;s annual meeting.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for 2017, 2018, and 2019, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Performance Share Units
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company has issued performance share units (PSUs) to its employees as part of the Company&#x2019;s long-term incentive program.&nbsp;&nbsp;There is a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	-year performance period associated with each PSU grant.&nbsp;&nbsp;The two performance measures applicable to all participants are the Company&#x2019;s return on invested capital and total stockholder return relative to those of the Company&#x2019;s pre-defined &#x201C;peer group.&#x201D;&nbsp;&nbsp;If the participant has met specified continued service requirements, the PSUs will settle in cash or a combination of cash and up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	50
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of equivalent value in the Company&#x2019;s common stock, at the discretion of the Compensation Committee of the Board of Directors.&nbsp;&nbsp;At December 31, 2016, there were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	368,394
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	PSUs outstanding (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	121,168
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	129,852
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	117,374
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	related to performance periods ending December 31, 2016, 2017 and 2018, respectively).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company has recorded both current and long-term liabilities for this liability-based compensation award.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	February 2014, the Company granted strategic performance share units (SPSUs) to the executive officers of the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;The number of target SPSUs was established at the beginning of a two-calendar year performance period.&nbsp;&nbsp;The final value of SPSUs earned was based upon the level of the Company&#x2019;s free cash flow achieved for 2015 and 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;All SPSU awards were paid out during 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Eligible employees are allowed to purchase shares of the Company&#x2019;s common stock at a discount during six-month offering periods beginning on January&nbsp;1 and July&nbsp;1 of each year and ending on June&nbsp;30 and December&nbsp;31 of each year, respectively.
</FONT>

<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:10.70%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #CCEEFF;HEIGHT:12.75PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;" NOWRAP="NOWRAP">
	332,467&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:01.72%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #CCEEFF;HEIGHT:12.75PT;PADDING:0PT;">

</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	401(k)/Profit Sharing Plan
</FONT>
<A NAME="SPN-20161231X10K_HTM_OLE_LINK37">
</A>
<A NAME="SPN-20161231X10K_HTM_OLE_LINK38">
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company maintains a defined contribution profit sharing plan for employees who have satisfied minimum service requirements.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employees may contribute up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	75
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of their eligible earnings to the plan subject to the contribution limitations imposed by the Internal Revenue Service.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company provides a nondiscretionary match of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	100
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of an employee&#x2019;s contributions to the plan, up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of the employee&#x2019;s salary.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company made contributions of $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	8.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million, $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	13.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million and $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	16.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million 2016, 2015 and 2014, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Non-Qualified Deferred Compensation Plans
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company has a non-qualified deferred compensation plan which allows senior management to defer up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	75
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of their base salary, up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	100
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of their bonus,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	100
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of the cash portion of their PSU compensation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and up to 100% of the vested RSUs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to the plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company also has a non-qualified deferred compensation plan for its non-employee directors which allows each director to defer up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	100
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% of their cash compensation paid by the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and up to 100% of the vested RSUs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to the plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;Payments are made to participants based on their annual enrollment elections and plan balances.&nbsp;&nbsp;Participants earn a return on their deferred compensation that is based on hypothetical investments in certain mutual funds.&nbsp;&nbsp;Changes in market value of these hypothetical participant investments are reflected as an adjustment to the deferred compensation liability of the Company with an offset to compensation expense.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company makes contributions that approximate the participant deferrals into various investments, principally life insurance that is invested in mutual funds similar to the participants&#x2019; hypothetical investment elections.&nbsp;&nbsp;Changes in market value of the investments and life insurance are reflected as adjustments to the deferred compensation plan asset with an offset to other income (expense) in the consolidated statements of operations.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The following table summarizes deferred compensation balances (in thousands):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Supplemental Executive Retirement Plan
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company has a supplemental executive retirement plan (SERP).&nbsp;&nbsp;The SERP provides retirement benefits to the Company&#x2019;s executive officers and certain other designated key employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;The SERP is an unfunded, non-qualified defined contribution retirement plan, and all contributions under the plan are unfunded credits to a notional account maintained for each participant.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under the SERP, the Company will generally make annual contributions to a retirement account based on age and years of service.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The participants in the plan receive contributions ranging from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	% to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	35
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	% of salary and annual cash bonus, which totaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	$2.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	million, $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	1.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	$1.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	million during 2016, 2015 and 2014, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company recorded compensation expense of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	$1.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	million,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	$2.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	$
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	million in general and administrative expenses during 2016, 2015 and 2014, respectively.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company may also make discretionary contributions to a participant&#x2019;s account.&nbsp;&nbsp;During
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2016, 2015 and 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, the Company paid $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$3.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million and $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million, respectively, to eligible
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	participants in the SERP.&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The net deferred tax assets reflect management&#x2019;s estimate of the amount that will be realized from future profitability and the reversal of taxable temporary differences that can be predicted with reasonable certainty.&nbsp;&nbsp;A valuation allowance has been recognized on a portion of the state net operating loss carryforward deferred tax asset.&nbsp;&nbsp;After considering all available evidence at December 31, 2016, the Company determined that it was more likely than not that a portion of the carryforward would not be realized.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accordingly, the Company increased deferred income tax expense by an additional
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	million of the valuation allowance.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT -18PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	At December 31, 2016, the Company had $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	320.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million in U.S. net operating loss carryforwards, which are available to reduce future or prior taxable income.&nbsp;&nbsp;The expiration dates for utilization of the loss carryforwards are 2021 through 2036.&nbsp;&nbsp;At December 31, 2016, the Company also had various state net operating loss carryforwards with expiration dates from 2017 to 2031.&nbsp;&nbsp;A net deferred tax asset of $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	26.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million reflects the expected future tax benefit for the state loss carryforwards.&nbsp;&nbsp;At December 31, 2016, the Company also had a U.S. foreign tax credit carryforward of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$49.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million with expiration dates from 2021 to 2026.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company has not provided U.S. income tax expense on earnings of its foreign subsidiaries, since the Company has reinvested or expects to reinvest outside the U.S. the undistributed earnings indefinitely.&nbsp;&nbsp;At December 31, 2016, the Company&#x2019;s foreign subsidiaries had an accumulated deficit in earnings.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company does not intend to repatriate the earnings of its foreign subsidiaries.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company has not provided U.S. income taxes for such earnings, except to the extent that such earnings were previously subject to U.S. income taxes.&nbsp;&nbsp;These earnings could become subject to U.S. income tax if remitted, or if deemed remitted as a dividend.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is not practicable to estimate the amount of taxes that might be payable on such undistributed earnings.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company files income tax returns in the U.S., including federal and various state filings, and certain foreign jurisdictions.&nbsp;&nbsp;The number of years that are open under the statute of limitations and subject to audit varies depending on the tax jurisdiction.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company remains subject to U.S. federal tax examinations for years after 2012.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company had unrecognized tax benefits of $29.9 million, $29.7 million and $30.3 million as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	December 31, 2016, 2015 and 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, respectively, all of which would impact the Company&#x2019;s effective tax rate if recognized.&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Business Segments
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Drilling Products and Services segment rents and sells bottom hole assemblies, premium drill pipe, tubulars and specialized equipment for use with onshore and offshore oil and gas well drilling, completion, production and workover activities.&nbsp;&nbsp;It also provides on-site accommodations and machining services.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Onshore Completion and Workover Services segment provides pressure pumping services used to complete and stimulate production in new oil and gas wells, fluid handling services and well servicing rigs that provide a variety of well completion, workover and maintenance services.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Production Services segment provides intervention services such as coiled tubing, cased hole and mechanical wireline, hydraulic workover and snubbing, production testing and optimization, and remedial pumping services.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Technical Solutions segment provides services typically requiring specialized engineering, manufacturing or project planning, including well containment systems, stimulation and sand control services and well plug and abandonment services.&nbsp;&nbsp;It also includes production handling arrangements and the production and sale of oil and gas.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company evaluates the performance of its reportable segments based on income or loss from operations.&nbsp;&nbsp;The segment measure is calculated as follows: segment revenues less segment operating expenses, depreciation, depletion, amortization and accretion expense, reduction in value of assets and allocated corporate general and administrative expenses.&nbsp;&nbsp;Corporate general and administrative expenses are allocated to the segments based primarily on specific identification and, to the extent that such identification is not practical, other methods which the Company believes to be a reasonable reflection of the utilization of services provided.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company believes this segment measure is useful in evaluating the performance of its reportable segments because it highlights operating trends and aids analytical comparisons.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s non-qualified deferred compensation plans allow officers, certain highly compensated employees and non-employee directors to defer receipt of a portion of their compensation and contribute such amounts to one or more hypotheti
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	cal investment funds (see note 6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company entered into separate trust agreements, subject to general creditors, to segregate assets of each plan and reports the accounts of the trusts in its consolidated financial statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;These investments are reported at fair value based on unadjusted quoted prices in active markets for identifiable assets and observable inputs for similar assets and liabilities, which represent Levels 1 and 2, respectively, in the fair value hierarchy.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	At December 31, 2016, the Company had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	interest rate swap agreements related to its fixed rate debt maturing in 2021 for notional amounts of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	$100
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	mil
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	lion each
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	(see note 11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	).

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#SPN-20161231X10K_HTM_TABLE_OF_CONTENT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 6PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	(11) Derivative Financial Instruments
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	From time to time, the Company may enter into interest rate swaps in an attempt to achieve a more balanced debt portfolio between fixed and variable debt.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company does not use derivative financial instruments for trading or speculative purposes.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	At December 31, 2016, the Company had three interest rate swaps for notional amounts of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$100
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million each
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	related to its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	7 1/8%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	senior notes maturing in December 2021.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	These transactions were designated as fair value hedges since the swaps hedged against the change in fair value of fixed rate debt resulting from changes in interest rates.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company recorded a derivative asset of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$8.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$6.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million within intangible and other long term assets in the consolidated balance sheets at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	December 31, 2016 and 2015, respectively, relating to these swaps
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The location and effect of the derivative instrument on the consolidated statements of operations presented on a pre-tax basis is as follows (in thousands):&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During 2016, 2015 and 2014 $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million, $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million and $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million of interest income, respectively, was related to the ineffectiveness associated with these fair value hedges.&nbsp;&nbsp;Hedge ineffectiveness represents the difference between the changes in fair value of the derivative instruments and the changes in fair value of the fixed rate debt attributable to changes in the benchmark interest rate.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Subsequent to year-end, during January 2017, the Company sold these interest rate swaps to the counterparties for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$0.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	(12) Discontinued Operations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During the first quarter of 2016, the Company&#x2019;s management determined that the conventional decommissioning business no longer met the held for sale criteria.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accordingly, property, plant and equipment related to the conventional decommissioning business was reclassified back to continuing operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	At December 31, 2016, the assets of the subsea construction business were being actively marketed and the Company&#x2019;s management was committed to selling the remaining assets, which were classified as held for sale and were included in the Technical Solutions segment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;

<A NAME="SPN-20161231X10K_HTM_PART_II_ITEM_9">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;">
	. Changes in and Disagreements with Accountants on Accounting and Financial Disclosure

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
